%N A396854 Number of digraphs on n unlabeled nodes with self-loops allowed and a distinguished node from which every node is reachable, counted up to isomorphism fixing the distinguished node.
%C A396854 Control-flow graphs with self-loops (a basic block may jump to itself) up to entry-preserving isomorphism.
%C A396854 Let r be the distinguished node. Then r reaches every node if and only if the strongly connected component containing r is the unique strongly connected component of indegree 0 in the condensation digraph. Thus this is the vertex-pointed analog of Robinson's construction for initially connected digraphs.
%C A396854 The corresponding count with self-loops forbidden equals A351052. A bijection is obtained by replacing every arc v->r by a loop v->v. The inverse replaces every loop v->v by the arc v->r. In the resulting digraph, r is the uniquely recoverable indegree-0 global source.
%D A396854 R. W. Robinson, Counting digraphs with restrictions on the strong components, in T.-H. Ku (ed.), Combinatorics and Graph Theory '95, World Scientific, Singapore, 1995, pp. 343-354.
%F A396854 The o.g.f. Sum_{n>=1} a(n)*x^n is obtained by the unlabeled specialization of D X (Point(S)*exp(-S)) in Robinson's cycle-index algebra for digraphs with loops. Here D and S are the cycle-index series for all digraphs and strongly connected digraphs, respectively; Point denotes vertex-pointing; and X is Robinson's special product.
%o A396854 (PARI) \\ See PARI link in A350794 for program code.
%o A396854 PointedInitially(graphs, yf=e->2)={my(E=InvGgfCIData(graphs, yf)); UnlabeledOgf(MulGgfCIData(graphs, MulCIData(PointCIData(-LogCIData(E)), E), yf))}
%o A396854 A396854seq(n)={Vec(PointedInitially(GraphCIData(n, DigraphWithLoopEdges)))}
%o A396854 A396854seq(14)
